description:
Cute studio in one of the most amazing neighborhoods in NYC located by 2nd Ave. Minutes away from the train and steps away from bars,coffee shops, restaurants, live music, Off Broadway shows. 24-hour grocery shops,Whole Foods market around the corner from F train metro.

Comfortable spot with a GREAT LOCALIZATION. Everything is WALKING DISTANCE: the iconic Saint Mark's street, Thompkin's Square, Union Square, SoHo, NoHo, Chinatown, West Village, Greenwich Village, Alphabet City. The apartment is on a quite street and you won't be bothered by outside noises.
There are plenty of coffee shops on every street if you feel like drinking your coffee outside. The studio itself is well-designed and makes the most of a small space. It is also MULTIFUNCTIONAL you can easily adjust it to your needs. It has wood floors, large windows, full kitchen, loft bed and two fold out sofa beds , it can accommodate up to 5 people. 
-WALKABLE TO THE BEST BARS , RESTAURANTS, ENTERTAINMENT VENUES IN TOWN,
-24 HOURS SHOPS AND RESTAURANTS,
-HIGH SPEED INTERNET,
-FLAT SCREEN TV

Full access to the apartment.

Let me know if you need anything. I am available on call or email to answer any of your questions or give you recommendations.

name: Multifunctional and Compact Studio

photos.caption: Loft bed and two pull out beds
Smart design solutions allow to convert the space to fit all your needs.
You can relax after the long day having a glass of wine and turn your bedroom into a spa-like sanctuary with aroma therapeutic Home Spa which is in the apartment.
Fully equipped kitchen with a blender for your delicious smoothies.There are couple of 24-hour grocery shops where you can buy anything any time you need.
Inside the little decorative house on the wall you can find Time Out New York magazines, City guides, discount tickets and some books.
Cheap and delicious pierogies and a lot more open 24 hours.
You can find them on 1st and 2nd avenue :)
Try one of the cereal soft-serve treats from the famous Momofuku Milk bar. It's walking distance.

Explore the iconic St Marks Place, which attracts hordes of people throughout the day and night to its bars, restaurants, karaoke spots, clothing stores, tattoo parlors, e-cigarette shops. The street on Friday and Saturday nights thrums with laughter, conversation and music until the early hours.
